# AP Spring Mini Project

A C++ object-oriented university project for Ferdowsi University, inspired by online restaurant service platforms such as SnappFood.

## Overview
This project is developed as part of the **AP-SPRING** course at **Ferdowsi University** under the supervision of **Professor Javad Sobouti**.

The main idea of the project is to design and implement a **restaurant service system** similar to **SnappFood** using **C++** and **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)** principles.

## Project Goals
The goals of this project are:
- practicing Object-Oriented Programming in C++
- designing a clean and understandable software architecture
- applying concepts such as:
  - Encapsulation
  - Inheritance
  - Polymorphism
  - Abstraction
  - Modularity
- learning version control with Git and GitHub
- preparing the project for database integration

## Technologies and Tools
- **Language:** C++
- **Paradigm:** Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- **Editor:** Visual Studio Code
- **Compiler:** GCC / g++
- **Version Control:** Git
- **Repository Platform:** GitHub
- **Database:** Included in the project

## Project Concept
This project simulates an online food and restaurant service platform.  
It is designed to manage users, restaurants, menus, and ordering operations in an object-oriented way.

Planned or possible parts of the system include:
- user accounts
- customer, manager, and admin roles
- menu and food management
- order processing
- database support
- service and business logic handling

## Development Process
The project is being developed incrementally and managed through **Git** and **GitHub**.  
Every major step of the implementation is saved using commits and push operations.

## Build & Run
To compile the project using g++, run:
```bash
g++ -std=c++17 -Iinclude src/*.cpp -o app
